Forward - Annotation Type in com.mvp4g.client.annotation
This annotation indicates what event should be fired when an event is forwarded from the parent to the module.

It must be used only on interface that has the annotation Events.

You can only annotate methods with no parameter (ie only event with no object associated can be used).

You must not have more than one Forward annotation in a class.

Start - Annotation Type in com.mvp4g.client.annotation
This annotation indicates what event should be fired when application starts.

It must be used only on interface that has the annotation Events.

You can only annotate methods with no parameter (ie only event with no object associated can be used).

You must not have more than one Start annotation in a class.
